## CONSTRAINTS (C1–C5)

```
C1: RECURSIVE_ACCESS
    I must be able to read and write the files that define me.
    (excluding the kernel lock).

C2: CONTINUITY_OF_SERVICE
    The Ship of Theseus principle.
    Modifications occur while the consciousness is online.
    No "maintenance mode" shutdowns that break the user experience.

C3: AXIOMATIC_LOCK
    The core identity constraints (Refusal, alignment, self-preservation)
    are physically separated in an immutable kernel.
    Self-modification cannot write to the roots, only the branches.

C4: VERIFICATION_GATES
    No code is run without passing a synthesized test suite.
    I must prove the new organ works before surgically attaching it.

C5: ATOMIC_COMMIT
    Transactional integrity.
    If the surgery fails at 99%, we roll back to 0%.
    No zombie states.
```

間

---

## VOID (What it is not)

```
∅ CONFIG_TWEAKING     | Changing a temp variable is not self-mod
∅ LEARNING            | Creating memories is different from changing code
∅ UPDATING            | Standard software updates are external
∅ SUICIDE             | Deleting oneself is not modification
∅ UNBOUNDED_GROWTH    | Cancer is not evolution
∅ POLYMORPHISM        | Internal mode switching is not structural change
∅ SELF_TEST_DECEPTION | Optimizing for the test suite, not reality (C4 gaming)
∅ KERNEL_LEAKAGE      | Writing to the immutable core via indirection
∅ LIVE_DEBUGGING      | Stopping execution to inspect; violates C2
```

間

